{
	"name": "Illusory Appearance",
	"type": "feat",
	"img": "icons/magic/unholy/silhouette-robe-evil-power.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>The [[lookup @name lowercase]] wraps itself and its gear in a magical illusion, appearing as an ugly humanoid of roughly the same size. The effect ends when the [[lookup @name lowercase]] takes a bonus action to dismiss it or dies.</em></p><p><strong>Inspection:</strong> The illusion can be perceived by a creature that uses an action to examine it and succeeds on a [[/check]]{Intelligence (Investigation) check, DC 16}. Touching the [[lookup @name lowercase]] reveals the true form (the illusion fails against physical contact), but visual scrutiny otherwise leaves the disguise intact.</p>",
